<TITLE> UK says no desire to hurt Moscow ties in ex-spy case </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 LONDON, June 1 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Britain rejected Russian allegations on Friday that it was politicising the case of murdered Kremlin critic Alexander Litvinenko. "We have no desire to aggravate diplomatic relations. We have consistently said that the murder of Mr Litvinenko is a very serious criminal matter which put hundreds of British citizens and visitors to the capital at risk," a Foreign Office spokesman said
